<p>I am trying to write a model in such a way that user chooses a choice first, then based on that choice I want to show other choices to user.</p>  <pre><code>from django.db import models  TOPIC_CHOICES = ( ('APTITUDE','APTITUDE'), ('ENGLISH','ENGLISH'), ) APTITUDE = ( ('NUMBER SYSTEM','NUMBER SYSTEM'), ('REASONING','REASONING'), ) ENGLISH = ( ('SYNONYMS','SYNONYMS'), ('ANTONYMS','ANTONYMS'), )  class Question(models.Model):     topic = models.CharField(choices=TOPIC_CHOICES, max_length=50)     sub_topic = models.CharField(choices=topic, max_length=50) </code></pre>  <p>for example if user chooses topic as APTITUDE then I have to show subtopic as 'NUMBER SYSTEM' and 'REASONING'.  How can I achieve this task? please help me.</p>